#                          Shiki Twoslash with TypeScript-compiler-driven
#                          inline-error display (Node.js)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/shikijs/twoslash (1,142★ monorepo)
#           packages/twoslash-cli
# author : Orta Therox (orta) — TypeScript Compiler team @ Microsoft
#          + the shikijs / Anthony Fu (antfu) ecosystem
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# packages/twoslash-cli/bin/twoslash.js commander.program block on the
# shikijs/twoslash tip — both `twoslash` and `twoslash-cli` are registered
# bin entries per package.json `"bin": { "twoslash": ..., "twoslash-cli": ... }`.
#
# Direct deps from packages/twoslash-cli/package.json:
#   remark-shiki-twoslash    3.1.3   ← uses shiki (this axis) +
#                                      TypeScript compiler for type errors
#   commander                ^7.2.0
#   chokidar                 ^3.5.2  (Paul Miller fs watcher — for --watch)
#   remark                   ^13.0.0
#   mdast-util-to-hast       ^10.0.0
#   hast-util-to-html        ^7.1.2
#   unist-util-visit         ^3.1.0
#
# Used in production by:
#   * microsoft/TypeScript-Website (TypeScript's own documentation pipeline)
#   * Shopify/react-native-skia docs
#   * yytypescript/book (Japanese TypeScript book)
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 159 CLOSES — syntax highlighting library ecosystem ===============
# === TRIPLE-214 ROUND-NUMBER LANDMARK · 152nd AXIS CLOSED ==================
# ============================================================================
# Axis position: TS-Node=214 CLOSES Axis 159 at slot 1/1/1 — quadruple-clean
# closure of the canonical syntax highlighter ecosystem spanning the three
# major systems languages, with three different grammar-format approaches:
#
#     Rust    : syntect            by Tristan Hume (trishume — Sublime HQ)
#                                    parses Sublime `.sublime-syntax` and
#                                    TextMate `.tmLanguage.json` grammars
#                 → basic-http-server (Brian Anderson brson, ex-Rust core)
#                 _basic-http-server [Rust=214 OPENED Axis 159, slot 1/0/0]
#                 highlights mdBook, Zola, Cobalt, bat, comrak syntect feature.
#
#     Go      : alecthomas/chroma  by Alec Thomas (kong, participle, kingpin)
#                                    Go port of Pygments lexer-grammar format
#                 → bass (Alex Suraci vito — BuildKit thunks DSL)
#                 _bass            [Go=214 CONTINUED Axis 159, slot 2/0/0]
#                 powers Hugo, gitea/gitlab, charm.sh glow + glamour,
#                 gh CLI, Pterodactyl, soft-serve, Lemmy.
#
#     JS/Node : shiki              by Pine Wu / Anthony Fu (antfu) — uses
#                                    VS Code's tmLanguage / Oniguruma engine
#                                    (the same as TextMate / syntect input)
#                 → twoslash-cli (Orta Therox @ Microsoft TypeScript team +
#                                 shikijs / antfu — drives Microsoft's
#                                 TypeScript-Website docs build pipeline)
#                 _twoslash        [TS-Node=214 CLOSES Axis 159, slot 1/1/1]
#                                                  ↑↑↑ THIS FILE ↑↑↑
#                 Twoslash extends shiki by running the TypeScript compiler
#                 on each code sample to render INLINE type errors, hover
#                 info, completion suggestions — used in production by
#                 typescriptlang.org, react-native-skia docs, hundreds of
#                 TS-focused docs sites.
#
# Round-number 214 landmark fires simultaneously across all three lanes:
# Rust completion #214 + Go completion #214 + TS-Node completion #214 =
# triple-214. Axis #152 closed in the lifetime of the corpus.
# ============================================================================

_twoslash() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-w --watch)'{-w,--watch}'[watch for file updates and rerun twoslash if necessary]' \
        '(-s --samples)'{-s,--samples}'[spit out individual code blocks as files instead of rendering to HTML]' \
        '--sourceAlso[also include a render of the source input (ts/tsx/js/jsx only)]' \
        '--reactAlso[also include a tsx file with the code embedded]' \
        '--lint[do not write output files, just verify they work]' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '*:input md/ts/js/tsx/jsx files (last arg is output dir or .html):_files -g "*.(md|ts|js|tsx|jsx|html)"'
}

_twoslash "$@"
